<div class="content" name="Introduction" uuid="996de171-1d35-4e7a-a436-80c88449d148"><p>The Service Witness Protocol is a remote procedure call
(RPC)-based protocol that is used to promptly notify a client of resource changes
that have occurred on a highly available server.</p><p>Sections 1.5, 1.8, 1.9, 2, and 3 of this specification are
normative. All other sections and examples in this specification are
informative.</p></div>